This project delivers a specialized AI agent designed to objectively measure and improve communication clarity in professional video meetings. By integrating high-fidelity ASR (Automatic Speech Recognition) with Large Language Model (LLM) semantic analysis, the agent provides a quantifiable metric‚Äîthe Meeting Clarity Index‚Äîto flag ambiguous language and excessive jargon.

‚ú® Key Features & Unique Contributions

This project moved beyond a standard tutorial by implementing advanced, real-world features:

Weighted Clarity Index (Scoring Logic): Calculates a nuanced score (0-100). The LLM assigns a penalty weight ($0.0 - 1.0$) to each jargon term based on its ambiguity, ensuring highly abstract buzzwords (synergy) are penalized more than common technical terms (Q4 goals).

Per-Speaker Contribution Analysis: Uses ASR Speaker Diarization data to track which individual speaker contributed the most jargon, enabling targeted communication coaching.

Structured Output & Auditing: The Gemini API is forced via a Pydantic schema to return a clean, machine-readable JSON report of jargon, weights, and critiques.

Highlighting & Review: Visually pinpoints every identified jargon term in the full transcript on the Streamlit dashboard.

‚öôÔ∏è Project Architecture and Technical Flow

The application executes a robust, three-stage pipeline  triggered by a video file upload:

Ingestion & Pre-processing (Python/MoviePy): Handles video extraction, duration validation, and ensures FFmpeg access via absolute path configuration.

ASR Layer (AssemblyAI): Transcribes audio and provides Speaker Diarization (identifying Speaker A, B, etc.).

LLM Semantic Analysis (Gemini/Mistral): Executes the core reasoning task. This layer supports switching between the high-reliability Cloud (Gemini) API and the low-cost Local (Ollama RAG) implementation, which grounds its analysis in the custom jargon_master_list.csv dataset.

Presentation (Streamlit): Synthesizes the results into a user-friendly dashboard with charts and color-coded metrics.

